In case of empty or missing topic it's failing. I addressed this issue into new patch with pattern match as below :

// valid kafka topic name regex
    private static final String TOPIC_NAME_PATTERN = "^[a-zA-Z0-9]([._-](?![._-])|[a-zA-Z0-9]){0,}[a-zA-Z0-9]$";
    protected static final Pattern topicPattern = Pattern.compile(TOPIC_NAME_PATTERN);

I normally do this as on line and use the ..._PATTERN name for the Pattern object!
(if need for complex or compounded regex expression I name the Strings ..._REGEX)

protected static final Pattern TOPIC_NAME_PATTERN = Pattern.compile("^[a-zA-Z0-9]([._-](?![._-])|[a-zA-Z0-9]){0,120}[a-zA-Z0-9]$");

I agree.. In swagger UI this example is shown as {  "topic": "(topic=my-topic-name)"}
The below should suffice :
topic: my-topic-name

